#. <section class="sutta" id="sn9.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga"
msgstr "1. In the Woods"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Sambahulasutta → sambahulāsuttaṃ (bj, pts2) | sambahulā (cārika) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn9.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Sambahulasutta"
msgstr "4. Several Mendicants Set Out Wandering"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.429"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.4:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ sambahulā bhikkhū kosalesu viharanti aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time several mendicants were staying in the land of the Kosalans in a "
"certain forest grove."

#. VAR: vassaṃvuṭṭhā → vassaṃ vutthā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn9.4:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū vassaṃvuṭṭhā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then after completing the three months of the rainy season residence, those "
"mendicants set out wandering."

msgctxt "sn9.4:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā te bhikkhū apassantī "
"paridevamānā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Not seeing those mendicants, the deity haunting that forest cried. And on "
"that occasion they recited this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.4:2.1"
msgid "“Arati viya mejja khāyati,"
msgstr "“Seeing so many vacated seats today,"

# BB’s note explains what he thinks the sense of this couplet is; but his translation doesn’t express that, at least to me.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:2.2"
msgid "Bahuke disvāna vivitte āsane;"
msgstr "it seems to me that they must have become dissatisfied."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:2.3"
msgid "Te cittakathā bahussutā,"
msgstr "They were so learned, such brilliant speakers!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:2.4"
msgid "Kome gotamasāvakā gatā”ti."
msgstr "Where have these disciples of Gotama gone?”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.4:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññatarā devatā taṃ devataṃ gāthāya paccabhāsi:"
msgstr "When they had spoken, another deity replied with this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.4:4.1"
msgid "“Māgadhaṃ gatā kosalaṃ gatā,"
msgstr "“They’ve gone to Magadha, they’ve gone to Kosala,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:4.2"
msgid "Ekacciyā pana vajjibhūmiyā;"
msgstr "and some are in the Vajjian lands."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:4.3"
msgid "Magā viya asaṅgacārino,"
msgstr "Like deer that wander free of ties,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:4.4"
msgid "Aniketā viharanti bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "the mendicants live with no abode.”"
